## Fixed Issues:

1. **`add(int index, E element)` method (lines 91-105)**: 
   - Fixed the bug where inserting at index 0 was incorrect
   - Now correctly handles:
     - Inserting at the beginning (index 0): creates a new node pointing to the current head, then updates head
     - Inserting elsewhere: finds the previous node and properly links in the new node
   - Added bounds checking

2. **`remove(Object obj)` method (lines 225-247)**:
   - Implemented the method to find and remove the first occurrence of the object
   - Handles removing from the head as a special case
   - Traverses the list to find the element to remove
   - Updates size and returns true if found, false otherwise

3. **`remove(int index)` method (lines 250-267)**:
   - Implemented the method to remove the element at the given index
   - Handles removing from the head as a special case
   - For other indices, finds the previous node and removes the target node
   - Returns the removed element and updates size
   - Includes bounds checking

All three methods should now work correctly. The code follows the linked list patterns used elsewhere in the class and handles edge cases (empty list, removing from head, etc.).

You can test these changes by running the JUnit tests once your test environment is properly configured. The methods should now pass all the test cases.
